{
  "analysis": "No valid /app/data.comp exists yet. The isolated integer tests show the encoder arithmetic/normalization is still wrong. The strongest grounded insight is that /app/decomp.c normalizes before computing `split`, so an exact mirror encoder should emit digits before computing split, using `fraction/range` state like the decoder. I need to validate this on the isolated integer-7 case first, testing both plausible stop-bit variants, before extending to the full file.",
  "plan": "Create `/tmp/enc_int_mirror.c` using `fraction/range` and normalization before split computation. It will encode `get_integer(9,0)` value 7. For the stop-bit count, I will test the direct mirror of `get_integer`: result has bit length `k+1`; `get_integer` increments `tmp` before each stop bit, reads zeros until it sees 1, then sets `tmp--`; so emit zeros for `t=start+1..start+k-1`, then a 1 at `start+k`, then `k` payload bits. Compile and run through `/tmp/dec_int`. If it decodes to 7, the core coder is validated. If not, I will inspect the trace.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat > /tmp/enc_int_mirror.c <<'C'
#include <stdio.h>
#include <stdlib.h>

#define RADIX 255

static long range = 1;
static long fraction = 0;
static int cc[2000000];

static void normalize_before(void){
    while(range < RADIX){
        long digit = fraction / RADIX;
        putchar((unsigned char)((digit + 1) & 0xFF));
        fraction = (fraction - digit * RADIX) * RADIX;
        range *= RADIX;
    }
}
static void put_bit(int ctx, int bit){
    normalize_before();
    int idx = ctx * 2;
    int c0 = cc[idx], c1 = cc[idx + 1];
    long split = range * (c0 + 1) / (c0 + c1 + 2);
    if(bit == 0){
        range = split;
    }else{
        fraction += split;
        range -= split;
    }
    cc[idx + bit]++;
    fprintf(stderr, "ENC ctx=%d bit=%d split=%ld fraction=%ld range=%ld c0=%d c1=%d\n", ctx, bit, split, fraction, range, c0, c1);
}
static void encode_integer(int start, int ctx, int value){
    long result = (long)value + (1L << start);
    int k = 0;
    while((1L << (k + 1)) <= result) k++;
    int ctx2 = ctx * 99;
    fprintf(stderr, "ENC value=%d result=%ld k=%d start=%d\n", value, result, k, start);
    for(int t = start + 1; t <= start + k - 1; t++) put_bit(t + ctx2, 0);
    put_bit(start + k + ctx2, 1);
    for(int i = k - 1; i >= 0; i--) put_bit(ctx, (int)((result >> i) & 1));
}
static void finish(void){
    normalize_before();
    for(int i = 0; i < 8; i++){
        long digit = fraction / RADIX;
        putchar((unsigned char)((digit + 1) & 0xFF));
        fraction = (fraction - digit * RADIX) * RADIX;
        range *= RADIX;
    }
}
int main(void){
    encode_integer(9, 0, 7);
    finish();
    return 0;
}
